name: JobRunner API Gateway
prefix: JBR
type: Unified Job Execution API
category: API Jobs & Streaming
description: REST/GraphQL API gateway for submitting, monitoring, and tailing long-running jobs. Supports batch, streaming, and cron-triggered execution modes. WebSocket live tail, RBAC per-job-type, OpenTelemetry distributed tracing, and full execution audit log.
features: REST + GraphQL job submission API, WebSocket live log tail, batch/stream/cron execution modes, RBAC per-job-type, OpenTelemetry tracing, execution audit log, job priority queue, retry with exponential backoff
design_bg: #0A0E1A
design_primary: #6366F1
design_vibe: Dark API indigo
budget: 850

name: BatchQueue Engine
prefix: BQE
type: Distributed Batch Job Processor
category: API Jobs & Streaming
description: High-throughput batch job engine with priority queues and worker pools. API-driven job submission with payload validation, parallel chunk processing, dead-letter queues for failed items, and real-time progress streaming via SSE.
features: Priority queue with fair scheduling, chunked parallel processing, SSE progress streaming, dead-letter queue, payload schema validation, worker pool auto-scaling, batch job audit trail, API rate limiting
design_bg: #0F172A
design_primary: #22C55E
